metadata.name: Organicum 1 #39
metadata.description:
Organicum 1 is the beginning of a journey I had in my mind for a long time: creating art with physics.

Physics are incredibly beautiful and fascinating but can also be intimidating. Obstacles, forces, attractors and collisions are just few of the many tools any common physics library provides and a creative use can generate very interesting art.

In future iterations I will try to add more species with more complex behaviors, evolving and interacting in time.

The scene is 1080x1080 pixels, pressing “S” you can save it as an image (Only in Live mode)

Yours,
CCDDBB

Made with Create.js and Matter.js - #tezos4tezos - 2022

metadata.name: Boro #113
metadata.description:
Boro is inspired by the Japanese mending technique of the same name, which means something mended, in particular something mended with small pieces of fabric and patterned over stitching. The technique makes the fabric both stronger and more beautiful.

To render at different resolutions please use keyboard characters 1 to 5, which will render the artwork at a square of 1000 to 5000 respectively.

metadata.name: Puzzles of the mind #86
metadata.description:
This is abstract art based on mathematical structure.
The puzzle of your mind seems broken and rearranged.

Mode has 2 variations.
 - Normal
 - Black
Color has 3 variations.
 - 常磐-tokiwa- (Green)
 - 真朱-shinshu- (Red)
 - 紺碧-konpeki- (Blue)
Color Level has 2 variations.
 - High
 - Low
Square Size has 3 variations.
 - Small
 - Middle
 - Large

Tokiwa is a Japanese word meaning always the same. It's green like the color of evergreen leaves.

Shinshu is a Japanese word that refers to a dull red color like vermilion. It means vermilion in its natural state with nothing mixed in.

Konpeki is a Japanese word that describes a deep blue, very close to azure. It's like a clear sky with summer sunshine.

Controls (in live view):
 - Press [f] to switch full screen on and off
 - Press [s] to download a PNG file with windowsize
 - Press [l] to download a PNG file with large size 4800 pixel (wait a minutes)

Create with p5.js

metadata.name: Fuschia Rubious Selenium #62
metadata.description:
"Fuschia Rubious Selenium" is a study of layered gradients and mask usage in p5js. There are two types of generation; controlled/contained and out-of-control. Controlled generations force shapes to be contained inside a margin around the canvas. The out-of-control generations allow the forms to escape the confinement of the canvas and include some other surprises. 

Press s to save the image.

metadata.name: Olive Aluminium Xenon #62
metadata.description:
"Olive Aluminium Xenon" explores using generative backgrounds to lead a field of isometric shapes. How the foreground and background interact varies wildly from generation to generation. Some generations resemble mountain ranges or mesas, some crystal fields or cityscapes. 

"Olive Aluminium Xenon" was created with p5.js.

metadata.name: tied #83
metadata.description:
"tied" is trying to represent the feeling of pressure over people.
To represent that I did an abstraction with points trapped by lines and dense textures, some of these points is stucked in the middle of the road, trying to get out of the background to reach surface.


this is my last contribution to fx beta.

a project made with p5.js and love to make part of it.


Omar Lobato Neto, 19/03/2022
